anabase and anabasis may also refer to :   art , entertainment , and media literature anabase ( 1924 ) , a poem by saint - john perse   anabasis , classic text by the greek writer xenophon ( 431–355 bc ) , about the expedition of the persian prince cyrus the younger against his brother , king artaxerxes   ii anabasis alexandri , classic text by the greek historian arrian ( 86 – after 146 ad ) , about alexander the great ( 336–323 bc )

the " x " games : in his " anabasis " this greek historian & soldier recounted an attack on persia in the 5th century b.c.

